# Rule: docs/adr/README.md

This file is the **only** file that ships in `docs/adr/` on day one. Until
the first numbered ADR lands, it carries the entire explanation of the
folder.

It must:

- state what an ADR is and is not (ADRs cover product/architecture decisions
  about a component or feature; they do not cover tooling, processes, or
  invariants);
- define the lifecycle (`proposed` / `accepted` / `superseded` / `deprecated`);
- show the format (frontmatter fields + the section list);
- cross-link `AGENTS.md §3` and `.agents/skills/navigating-project-docs/`.

It must **not** exceed ~120 lines.
